pan></a> Now is the time for countries with
influence over the Iraqi government, Iraq&rsquo;s religious class, and the =
various
ethnic and sectarian communities to push for a resolution to the crisis tha=
t
moves Iraq beyond Prime Minister Maliki&rsquo;s zero-sum sectarian politics=
. As part
of the reported direct dialogue between the United States and Iran, the Uni=
ted States
should emphasize that the sort of majoritarian politics Iran has encouraged=
